HEADWORD: Decorticator
<hw>De*cor"ti*ca`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A machine for
decorticating wood, hulling grain, etc.; also, an instrument for
removing surplus bark or moss from fruit trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

